Figure Captions Fig. 1: Sensitivity of present and future accelerator and reactor experiments to neutrino oscillations, charted in the (hL=Ei; Pmin) and (\Delta m2min; sin2 2`min) coordinates. The initial (ff, prepared) and final (fi, detected) neutrino flavors are also indicated (ff ! fi). See the text for details.

Fig. 2: Triangular plot representation of the neutrino state *3, in terms of its flavor

components *e, *_, *o/ . For a triangle of unit height, the unitarity relation U 2e3 + U 2_3 + U 2o/3 = 1 is enforced by identifying the U 2ff3 with the three distances from *3 to the sides (dashed lines). The "general 3* oscillation" scenario and its "2* oscillation" and "no oscillation" limits are represented respectively by the region inside, by the sides, and by the corners of the triangle. Iso-lines of sin2 and sin2 OE (parametrizing the elements Uff3) are charted in the lower plot.

Fig. 3: Iso-lines of oscillation probability P (P = Pfffi or P = 1 \Gamma Pffff) in the triangular

plot defined in Fig. 2, for various channels (ff $ fi) and large m2, such that sin2(1:27\Delta m2L=E) ' 1=2. In the case of no oscillation, iso-P lines delimit excluded regions. A qualitative combination of null results in all channels is shown in the plot labeled "ALL," where the corners belong to the allowed zone.

Fig. 4: As in Fig. 3, but in the bilogarithmic (tg2; tg2OE) representation. Notice the

deformation of the iso-P contours due to the 4 ! 2 mapping. Here the *e, *_ and *o/ flavor eigenstates are reached respectively in the limits: tg2OE ! 1 (any tg2); tg2OE ! 0 and tg2 ! 1; tg2OE ! 0 and tg2 ! 0.

Fig. 5: Curves of iso-R (double flavor ratio) for atmospheric neutrinos, at large m2

(i.e., sin2(1:27 \Delta m2L=E) ' 1=2), in both the triangular and the (tg2; tg2OE) representation. A "typical" experimental result as R = 0:5 \Sigma 0:2 would correspond to the allowed region inside the two R = 0:7 lines. Notice that the pure two-oscillation solutions e $ _ (right-hand side) and _ $ o/ (bottom side) are smoothly connected here. See the text for the case m2 !, 0:01 eV2.

Fig. 6: Two-flavor exclusion plots at the 90% and 99% C.L. for the G"osgen, Bugey,

Krasnoyarsk, E531, CDHSW and E776 experiments, as derived by our reanalysis of the raw data. The solid contours agree well with the original 90% C.L. bounds published in the quoted references of the different experiments.

Fig. 7: Three-flavor exclusion plots at the 90% and 99% C.L. in the (tg2; tg2OE) representation, as derived by the experimental data analyzed in the various oscillation channels (ff $ fi), and in all channels combined (ALL) for m2 = 20 eV2.

