Fig. 13: Comparison, at m2 = 0:01 eV2, between the region qualitatively favored by the

atmospheric neutrino data (dotted lines), and the sensitivity region of future short and long baseline experiments (solid lines). Notice that the neutrino oscillation solution to the atmospheric anomaly can be completely probed by future _ ! _ disappearance experiments (e.g., BNL E889), as well as by the combined _ ! e and _ ! o/ appearance searches (as in the "CERN to ICARUS at G.S." proposal).

